<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1435,1898,2036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Remark: 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad" box="[265,474,1973,1999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Lundblad, O. (1969) Indische Wassermilben, hauptsachlich aus Hinterindien. Arkiv for Zoology, 22, 1 - 126." type="journal article" year="1969">
Lundblad (
<number box="[401,465,1973,1999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1969.0">1969</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Daday, 1898" authorityName="Daday" authorityYear="1898" box="[626,957,1973,1999]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[626,771,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Oxus pictus</emphasis>
(Daday, 
<number box="[885,948,1973,1999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1898.0">1898</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
to be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName box="[1264,1429,1973,1998]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisetus">
<emphasis box="[1264,1429,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1289,1973,1998]" name="Iceland" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O</collectingCountry>
. longisetus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[471,622,2010,2036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">
Cook (
<number box="[550,613,2010,2036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the long distal setae of Cx-I are not curved in 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1277,2011,2036]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1277,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<collectingCountry box="[1171,1195,2011,2036]" name="Iceland" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O</collectingCountry>
. pictus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
